<TEXT>
Sir, Lex makes the point that some unit trust managers are against the
Securities and Investments Board proposals, because it would be 'more
difficult for them to make profits by holding units on their own account
ready for resale' ('Unit trusts', October 22).
Somewhat similar behaviour by stockbrokers and traders has been punished
severely by stock exchanges everywhere.
Could you publish a list of unit trusts which do not engage in this practice
and also an interview with a fund manager who does? The interview should
