FT  26 OCT 93 / Lady Thatcher speaks out on Gatt talks
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE US might withdraw military protection from Europe if the European
Community fails to reach a compromise deal on the Uruguay Round of Gatt
trade talks, Lady Thatcher said yesterday.
Addressing the American Chamber of Commerce in London, she said that a US
military withdrawal would be 'very serious indeed for the world as a whole'.
She said the US presence in Europe was 'all of a piece with co-operating
together on the international economy under the Gatt'.
Singling out France for special criticism, she said hopes of a Gatt deal
were threatened by a long-standing 'anti-American streak' in the EC.
