<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 93 / Gainsborough sold for record Pounds 3.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A GAINSBOROUGH landscape, 'Peasants going to market, early morning' has been
sold by Royal Holloway College, Esher, Surrey, for Pounds 3.5m, a record for
the 18th-century English artist.
The picture was sold to raise money for an endowment fund.
