FT  26 OCT 93 / World Trade News: Siemens expands in China
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BAXTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SIEMENS, the German electrical and electronics group, is expanding in the
Chinese power plant market through a joint venture to make instrumentation
and control equipment there.
The venture, Siemens Power Plant Automation, will be 60 per cent-owned by
Siemens, with the balance held by Nanjing Electric Power Automation
Equipment General Factory, controlled by the Chinese ministry for the
electric power industry.
The venture will be based in in Nanjing, 150 miles from Shanghai, and will
employ about 100 people.
