<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 93 / Hijackers seize Nigerian aircraft
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NIAMEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ARMED hijackers claiming to be supporters of Nigerian politician Moshood
Abiola yesterday seized a Nigeria Airways A310 Airbus with 149 people
aboard, and demanded Mr Abiola's immediate installation as president,
airport officials at Niamey in neighbouring Niger said, Reuter reports from
Niamey.
Nigerian officials said there were five hijackers and that the chairman of
the National Electoral Commission Okon Uya and former oil minister Jibril
Aminu were on the aircraft.
The hijackers later freed 125 of the passengers and crew but said they had
sprinkled the cabin with petrol and would blow the aircraft up unless it
flew to Frankfurt.
Aides for Mr Abiola, widely believed to have won presidential elections last
June which were annulled by the then-military government, said he had
nothing to do with the hijack.
