<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 93 / Cragnotti inquiry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Sergio Cragnotti, the Rome businessman closely linked to the Ferruzzi
family, has been advised he is under investigation for alleged falsification
of financial information, writes Robert Graham in Rome.
The move coincided with police raids on Mr Cragnotti's offices in Milan and
Rome and the removal of documents for inspection by Ravenna magistrates. The
latter, along with Milan magistrates, are conducting twin investigations
into the affairs of the collapsed Ferruzzi empire, Italy's second largest
private group.
Mr Cragnotti, chairman of the Lazio football team, currently runs his own
agri-business and foodstuffs trading company.
