<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 93 / International Company News: London &amp; St Lawrence merger
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LONDON &amp; St Lawrence Investment Company is making an agreed offer for its
fellow investment trust, Practical Investment Company, creating a trust with
assets of about Pounds 58m.
London is offering shares based on the relative formula asset values. It
already holds 27.4 per cent and has irrevocable acceptances for a further
54.4 per cent.
Both trusts have similar investment policies and have been closely
associated since 1957. In 1990 London voted to continue until at least the
1993 annual meeting and in accordance with its articles a motion is to be
put to the next annual meeting to put Practical into voluntary liquidation.
London also reported that its net asset value per share at August 31 was
175.32p, against 124.82p a year earlier.
Net revenue for the 12 months to the end of August was Pounds 836,600
(Pounds 827,000). Earnings per share were 4.39p (4.34p).
An interim dividend of 3.64p has been declared, against last year's single
final payment of 3.36p, with an unchanged special dividend of 0.48p.
