<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 93 / Observer: Run out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Well done the Toronto Blue Jays. Last year, Canada's constitutional
referendum coincided with the Blue Jays' victory parade, after the baseball
players became the first non-US team to win the World Series. In an encore
this weekend, they comfortably retained the title ahead of today's general
election.
Sadly, Blue Jay-induced euphoria bodes ill for the ruling Progressive
Conservative party. Last year, Brian Mulroney's constitutional proposal was
firmly rejected, and now it looks as if Mulroney's successor, Kim Campbell,
is poised for a resounding defeat. She could always take up baseball.
</TEXT>
