<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 93 / Retailers low in European ranking
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RETAILERS in the UK have 'startlingly low' levels of turnover per employee
compared with the rest of Europe, a survey of 16 countries by the Economist
Intelligence Unit says.
Ranking 131 companies by turnover per employee, the unit found that Kwik
Save, the discount food chain, was the highest UK company in 43rd place.
